22https://www.douban.com/. We select two CDSR scenarios for experiments: “Book-Movie” and “Book-Music”. To ensure sequential constraints, we retain cross-domain interaction sequences that include at least 3 items from each domain within one year. Ratings greater than 3 are considered positive feedback, while ratings less than or equal to 3 are considered negative feedback. We preprocess the data into a sequential recommendation format and split it based on timestamp records: the first 80% serves as the training set, the next 10% as the validation set, and the final 10% as the test set. Statistics are provided in Table 1.
